    <section class="section">
        <h1 id="ingredients">Ingredients Needed:</h1>
        <div class= "ingredient-main-box">

            <div class="ingredient-container">
                <div class="ingredient-boxes">
                    <b>MEAT</b>
                    <hr>
                    <ul>
                        <li>1 Pound Sweet Italian Sausage</li>
                        <li>3/4 Pound Lean Ground Beef</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
    
                <div class="ingredient-boxes">
                    <b>TOMATO PRODUCTS</b>
                    <hr class="new1">
                    <ul>
                        <li>1 Can (28 Ounces) of Crushed Tomatoes</li>
                        <li>2 Cans (6.5 Ounces) of Canned Tomato Sauce</li>
                        <li>2 Cans (6 Ounce) of Tomato Paste</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
    
                <div class="ingredient-boxes">
                    <b>SPICES</b>
                    <hr class="new1">
                    <ul>
                        <li>4 Tablespoons of Chopped Fresh Parsley</li>
                        <li>1 ½ Teaspoons of Dried Basil Leaves</li>
                        <li>½ Teaspoon of Fennel Seeds</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
    
                <div class="ingredient-boxes">
                    <b>EGGS & NOODLES</b>
                    <hr class="new1">
                    <ul>
                        <li>1 Large Egg</li>
                        <li>12 Lasagna Noodles</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
    
            <div class="ingredient-container">
                <div class="ingredient-boxes">
                    <b>ONION & GARLIC</b>
                    <hr class="new1">
                    <ul>
                        <li>1/4 Cup of Minced Onions</li>
                        <li>2 Cloves of Garlic, Crushed</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="ingredient-boxes">
                    <b>SEASONINGS</b>
                    <hr class="new1">
                    <ul>
                        <li>1/4 Teaspoon of Ground Blackpepper</li>
                        <li>1 ½ Teaspoons of Salt to Taste</li>
                        <li>2 Tablespoons of White Sugar</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="ingredient-boxes">
                    <b>CHEESES</b>
                    <hr class="new1">
                    <ul>
                        <li>16 Ounces of Ricotta Cheese</li>
                        <li>3/4 Pound of Mozzarella Cheese, Sliced</li>
                        <li>3/4 Pound of Grated Parmesan Cheese</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!--Process Part-->
    <section class="section-process">
        <h1 id="process">Cooking & Layering Lasagna</h1>
        <div class="video-container">
            <video controls autoplay muted>
                <source src="chapter 1 - videos/How to Make the Worlds Best Lasagna ｜ Allrecipes.com.mp4" type="video/mp4"> 
            </video>
        </div>


        <div class="process-container">

            <div class="left">
                <h2>How to Cook Lasagna</h2>
                <ol>
                    <li>Make the meat sauce:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Cook sausage, ground beef, onion, and garlic in a <br>Dutch soven over medium heat until well browned.</li>
                            <li>Stir in crushed tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, and water. <br>Season with sugar, 
                                2 tablespoons parsley, basil, 1 teaspoon salt, Italian <br> seasoning, fennel seeds, and pepper. 
                                Simmer, covered, for about 1 ½ hours, <br> stirring occasionally.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
    
                    <li>Cook the noodles:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. 
                                <br>Cook lasagna noodles in boiling water for 8 to 10 minutes. <br>Drain noodles, and rinse with cold water.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
    
                    <li>Make the ricotta mixture:
                        <ul>
                            <li>In a mixing bowl, combine ricotta cheese with egg, <br>remaining 2 tablespoons parsley, and 1/2 teaspoon salt.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
    
                    <li>Preheat the oven:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
    
                    <li>Layer the lasagna</li>
    
                    <li>Cover with foil and bake: 
                        <ul>
                            <li>Cover with foil: to prevent sticking, either spray 
                                <br>foil with cooking spray or make sure the foil does not touch the cheese.</li>
                            <li>Bake in the preheated oven for 25 minutes. <br>Remove the foil and bake for an additional 25 minutes.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
    
                    <li>Let the lasagna rest for 15 minutes before serving.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
    
            <div class="right">
                <h2>HOW TO LAYER LASAGNA</h2>
                    <p>Here is how you properly layer your lasagna:</p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Meat sauce
                            <ul>
                                <li>To assemble, spread 1 ½ cups of meat sauce in the bottom of a 9x13-inch baking dish.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>Noodles
                            <ul>
                                <li>Arrange 6 noodles lengthwise over meat sauce, overlapping slightly.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>Ricotta mixture
                            <ul>
                                <li>Spread with 1/2 of the ricotta cheese mixture.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>Mozzarella slices
                            <ul>
                                <li>Top with 1/3 of the mozzarella cheese slices. </li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>Meat sauce
                            <ul>
                                <li>Spoon 1 ½ cups meat sauce over mozzarella</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>Parmesan cheese
                            <ul>
                                <li>Sprinkle with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>Repeat the layers, then top with the remaining Parmesan</li>
                    </ol>
            </div>
    
        </div>
        
    </section>

